40 // Base class for all graph-based dynamic planners. These planners are all
41 // guaranteed to generate recursively feasible trajectories constructed
42 // using sampling-based logic.
43 //

76  // Recursive version of Plan() that plans outbound and return trajectories.
77  // High level recursive feasibility logic is here. Keep track of the
78  // graph of explored states, a set of goal states, the start time,
79  // whether or not this is an outbound or return trip, and whether
80  // or not to extract a trajectory at the end (if not, returns an empty one.)
81  Trajectory<S> RecursivePlan(SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >& graph,
82  const SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >& goals,
83  double start_time,
84  bool outbound,
85  const ros::Time& initial_call_time) const;

87  // Generate a sub-plan that connects two states and is dynamically feasible
88  // (but not necessarily recursively feasible).
89  virtual Trajectory<S> SubPlan(
90  const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time=0.0) const = 0;

92  // Cost functional. Defaults to time, but can be overridden.

181 // Plan a trajectory from the given start to goal states starting
182 // at the given time.
183 template<typename S, typename E,
184  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
185 Trajectory<S> GraphDynamicPlanner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::
186 Plan(const S& start, const S& goal, double start_time=0.0) const {
187  // Keep track of initial time.
188  const ros::Time initial_call_time = ros::Time::now();
189 
190  // Set up start and goal nodes.
191  Node<S>::Ptr start_node;
192  start_node->state = start;
193  start_node->time = start_time;
194  start_node->cost_to_come = 0.0;
195  start_node->is_viable = true;
196 
197  Node<S>::Ptr goal_node;
198  goal_node->state = goal;
199  goal_node->time = constants::kInfinity;
200  goal_node->cost_to_come = constants::kInfinity;
201  goal_node->is_viable = true;
202 
203  // Generate trajectory.
204  const Trajectory<S> traj =
205  RecursivePlan(SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >(start_node),
206  SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >(goal_node),
207  start_time, true, initial_call_time);
208 
209  // Wait around if we finish early.
210  const double elapsed_time = (ros::Time::now().toSec() - initial_call_time.toSec());
211  if (elapsed_time < max_runtime_)
212  ros::Duration(max_runtime_ - elapsed_time).sleep();
213 
214  return traj;
215 }

218 // Recursive version of Plan() that plans outbound and return trajectories.
219 // High level recursive feasibility logic is here.
220 template<typename S, typename E,
221  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
222 Trajectory<S> GraphDynamicPlanner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::
223 RecursivePlan(SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >& graph,
224  const SearchableSet< Node<S>, S >& goals,
225  double start_time,
226  bool outbound,
227  const ros::Time& initial_call_time) const {
228  // Loop until we run out of time.
229  while ((ros::Time::now().toSec() - initial_call_time.toSec()) < max_runtime_) {
230  // (1) Sample a new point.
231  const S sample = S::Sample(lower, upper);
232 
233  // (2) Get k nearest neighbors.
234  const std::vector< Node<S>::Ptr > neighbors =
235  graph.KnnSearch(sample, num_neighbors_);
236 
237  Node<S>::Ptr parent = nullptr;
238  for (const auto& neighbor : neighbors) {
239  // Reject this neighbor if it's too close to the sample.
240  if ((neighbor->state.ToVector() - sample.ToVector()).norm() <
241  constants::kEpsilon)
242  continue;
243 
244  // (3) Plan a sub-path from this neighbor to sampled state.
245  const Trajectory<S> sub_plan =
246  SubPlan(neighbor->state, sample, neighbor->time);
247 
248  if (sub_plan.Size() > 0) {
249  parent = neighhor;
250 
251  // Add to graph.
252  Node<S>::Ptr sample_node = Node<S>::Create();
253  sample_node->state = sample;
254  sample_node->time = parent->time + sub_plan.Duration();
255  sample_node->cost_to_come = parent->cost_to_come + Cost(sub_plan);
256  sample_node->is_viable = false;
257  sample_node->best_parent = parent;
258  sample_node->children = {};
259  sample_node->trajs_to_children = {};
260 
261  // Update parent.
262  parent->children.push_back(sample_node);
263  parent->trajs_to_children.push_back(sub_plan);
264 
265  break;
266  }
267  }
268 
269  // Sample a new point if there was no good way to get here.
270  if (parent == nullptr)
271  continue;
272 
273  // (4) Connect to one of the k nearest goal states if possible.
274  std::vector< Node<S>::Ptr > neighboring_goals =
275  goals.RadiusSearch(sample, search_radius_);
276 
277  Node<S>::Ptr child = nullptr;
278  for (const auto& goal : neighboring_goals) {
279  // Check if this is a viable node.
280  if (!goal->is_viable)
281  continue;
282 
283  // Try to connect.
284  const Trajectory<S> sub_plan =
285  SubPlan(sample, goal->state, sample_node->time);
286 
287  // Upon success, set child to point to goal and update sample node to
288  // include child node and corresponding trajectory.
289  if (sub_plan.Size() > 0) {
290  child = goal;
291 
292  // Update sample node to point to child.
293  sample_node->children.push_back(child);
294  sample_node->trajs_to_children.push_back(sub_plan);
295 
296  break;
297  }
298  }
299 
300  if (child == nullptr) {
301  // (5) If outbound, make a recursive call.
302  if (outbound)
303  const Trajectory<S> ignore =
304  RecursivePlan(graph, graph, sample_node->time,
305  false, initial_call_time);
306  } else {
307  // Reached the goal. Update goal to ensure it always has the
308  // best parent.
309  if (child->best_parent == nullptr ||
310  child->best_parent->cost_to_come > sample_node->cost_to_come) {
311  // I'm yo daddy.
312  child->best_parent = sample_node;
313 
314  // Breath first search to update time / cost to come.
315  UpdateDescendants(sample_node);
316  }
317 
318  // Make sure all ancestors are viable.
319  // NOTE! Worst parents are not going to get updated.
320  Node<S>::Ptr parent = sample_node;
321  while (parent != nullptr && !parent->is_viable) {
322  parent->is_viable = true;
323  parent = parent->best_parent;
324  }
325 
326  // Extract trajectory. Always walk backward from the initial node of the
327  // goal set to that of the start set.
328  // Else, return a dummy trajectory since it will be ignored anyway.
329  if (outbound)
330  return ExtractTrajectory(graph.InitialNode(), goals.InitialNode())
331  else
332  return Trajectory<S>();
333  }
334  }
335 
336  // Ran out of time.
337  ROS_ERROR("%s: Planner ran out of time.", name_.c_str());
338 
339  // Don't return a trajectory if not outbound.
340  if (!outbound)
341  return Trajectory<S>();
342 
343  // Return a viable loop if we found one.
344  const Node<S>::ConstPtr start = graph.InitialNode();
345  if (start->best_parent == nullptr) {
346  ROS_ERROR("%s: No viable loops available.", name_.c_str());
347  return Trajectory<S>();
348  }
349 
350  ROS_INFO("%s: Found a viable loop.", name_.c_str());
351  return ExtractTrajectory(start, start);
352 }

354 // Extract a trajectory from goal node to start node if one exists.
355 // Returns empty trajectory if none exists.
356 template<typename S, typename E,
357  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
358 Trajectory<S> GraphDynamicPlanner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::
359 ExtractTrajectory(const Node<S>::ConstPtr& start,
360  const Node<S>::ConstPtr& goal) const {
361  // Accumulate trajectories in a list.
362  std::list< Trajectory<S> > trajs;
363 
364  Node<S>::Ptr node = goal;
365  while (node != start || (node == start && trajs.size() == 0)) {
366  const Node<S>::Ptr parent = node->best_parent;
367 
368  if (parent == nullptr) {
369  ROS_ERROR("%s: Parent was null.", name_.c_str());
370  break;
371  }
372 
373  // Find node as child of parent.
374  // NOTE! Could avoid this by replacing parallel std::vectors
375  // an std::unordered_map.
376  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < parent->children.size(); ii++) {
377  if (parent->children[ii] == node) {
378  trajs.push_front(parent->trajs_to_children[ii]);
379  break;
380  }
381 
382  if (ii == parent->children.size() - 1)
383  ROS_ERROR("%s: Parent/child inconsistency.", name_.c_str());
384  }
385  }
386 
387  // Concatenate into a single trajectory.
388  return Trajectory<S>(trajs);
389 }

391 // Load parameters.
392 template<typename S, typename E,
393  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
394 bool GraphDynamicPlanner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::
395 LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
396  if (!Planner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::LoadParameters(n))
397  return false;
398 
399  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
400 
401  // Search parameters.
402  int k;
403  if (!nl.getParam("planner/search_radius", search_radius_)) return false;
404  if (!nl.getParam("planner/num_neighbors", k)) return false;
405  num_neighbors_ = static_cast<size_t>(k);
406 
407  return true;
408 }

410 // Update cost to come, time, and all traj_to_child times recursively.
411 template<typename S, typename E,
412  typename D, typename SD, typename B, typename SB>
413 void GraphDynamicPlanner<S, E, D, SD, B, SB>::
414 UpdateDescendants(const Node<S>::Ptr& node,
415  const Node<S>::ConstPtr& start) const {
416  // Run breadth-first search.
417  // Initialize a queue with 'node' inside.
418  std::list< Node<S>::Ptr > queue = { node };
419 
420  while (queue.size() > 0) {
421  // Pop oldest node.
422  const Node<S>::Ptr current_node = queue.front();
423  queue.pop_front();
424 
425  // Skip this one if it's the start node.
426  if (current_node == start)
427  continue;
428 
429  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < current_node->children.size(); ii++) {
430  const Node<S>::Ptr child = current_node->children[ii];
431 
432  // Push child onto the queue.
433  queue.push_back(child);
434 
435  // Update trajectory to child.
436  // NOTE! This could be removed since trajectory timing is adjusted
437  // again upon concatenation and extraction.
438  current_node->trajs_to_children[ii].ResetFirstTime(current_node->time);
439 
440  // Maybe update child's best parent to be the current node.
441  // If so, also update time and cost to come.
442  if (child->best_parent != nullptr ||
443  child->best_parent->cost_to_come > current_node->cost_to_come) {
444  child->best_parent = current_node;
445 
446  child->time = current_node->time +
447  current_node->trajs_to_children[ii].Duration();
448  child->cost_to_come = current_node->cost_to_come +
449  Cost(current_node->trajs_to_children[ii]);
450  }
451  }
452  }
453 }
